sentences.english: Here we arrived at end of a very scenic Tad Sae waterfalls.
sentences.chinese: 在這裏，我們在一個非常優美塔德世瀑布年底抵達。

sentences.english: Wu left Wellington for Auckland by a special plane on the morning of May 27.
sentences.chinese: 吳邦國是27日上午乘專機離開惠靈頓抵達奧克蘭的。

sentences.english: A group of armed guards have arrived and are waiting outside the gate.
sentences.chinese: 一隊武裝警衛抵達並守衛在牢房區大門處。

sentences.english: The voyage lasted 46 minutes, from its departure in Philadephia to its landing across the Delaware River.
sentences.chinese: 從費城出發抵達特拉華河對面的旅程持續了46分鐘。

sentences.english: We have arrived in Tsuen Wan, please exit from the train, thank you.
sentences.chinese: 本班列車已經抵達荃灣站，請所有乘客落車，多謝。

sentences.english: Upon arrival you will have the local kampong style breakfast.
sentences.chinese: 抵達後，體驗富有當地部落風俗的早餐。

sentences.english: Mr. Day is expected to have arrived by now.
sentences.chinese: 戴先生現在應該要抵達了。

sentences.english: 20am : Members of foreign royal families arrive at the Abbey from Buckingham Palace.
sentences.chinese: 國外皇室成員抵達教堂。

sentences.english: The Britishmen arrived on the American coasts.
Eventually, the algorithm reaches a leaf node with the final classification.
sentences.chinese: 最終，算法抵達的葉子節點就是最終分類。

sentences.english: They arrived at the port of Inchon on the northwest coast.
sentences.chinese: 他們抵達仁川港西北海岸。

sentences.english: At present, they are visiting all parts of the country. They will be arriving here tomorrow.
sentences.chinese: 目前他們正在全國各地巡迴上演，今天就要抵達此地。

sentences.english: Send me a postcard when you get to New York.
sentences.chinese: 抵達紐約時寄張明信片給我。

sentences.english: President Obama will get down to business soon after his arrival in Moscow.
sentences.chinese: 奧巴馬總統一經抵達莫斯科後將會專注於正事。

sentences.english: The first steamboat to reach the city, in 1812, was appropriately called the New Orleans.
sentences.chinese: 第一艘蒸汽船於1812年抵達叫新奧爾良的城市。
